MISC
WORN_DON
*DESCRIPTION_START
This is a small elegant chain that is linked in the center by a large catseye inset within a smooth brace of polished platinum. The ferronniere is extemely well made as far as you can tell and the jewel in the center seems to pulse along with your heartbeat as you look at it. Upon closer examination you see that the chain is comprised of very very small, riveted layers that mesh and intertwine in a dazzlingly intricate pattern. This is a true thing of beauty.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFPREVERB GET -1
 IFVAR INTNUM3 = 1
  ECHO PLAYER ::: AUCTION ITEM ::::
  ECHO PLAYER ::: Report any problems with this item to Tannelorn. :::
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB RECALL -1
 SKILLCHECK 32 5 TANNSPLUB
 IFVAR TANNSPLUB > 0
  ECHO PLAYER You remember reading the following passage in a book somewhere...
  ECHO PLAYER ------%c-----%c----
  ECHO PLAYER This item of jewlery is a thin chain worn around the forehead with a small
  ECHO PLAYER jewel set into the center. The ferronniere is worn exclusively by ladies of the
  ECHO PLAYER upper class. The wearing of a ferronniere is considered an elegant touch within
  ECHO PLAYER the aristocracy. An adventurer hoping to impress someone of high station might
  ECHO PLAYER benefit from wearing a tasteful ferronniere.
  ECHO PLAYER ----%c-----%c------
 ELSE
  ECHO PLAYER You can't remember what a ferronniere is.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB CONCENTRATE -1
 CLEARVERB
 IFITEM -1 WORN
  ECHO PLAYER You close your eyes and touch your finger to the catseye in the center of the ferronniere.
  ECHO OTHERS %n closes %h eyes and touches two fingers to the catseye in the center of %h ferronniere.
  IFVAR ITEMVAL3 ! TIM
   SPELL 520 25
   SETITEMVAL -1 3 TIM
  ELSE
   ECHO ALL Nothing happens.
  ENDIF
 ELSE
  ECHO PLAYER You are not wearing that.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PUSH -1
 CLEARVERB
 IFITEM -1 WORN
  ECHO PLAYER You sink deeply into your thoughts, pressing your palm against the catseye on your forehead.
  ECHO OTHERS %n presses %h palm against the catseye on %h forehead and sinks deeply into thought.
 ELSE
  ECHO PLAYER You are not wearing that.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB TURN -1
 CLEARVERB
 IFITEM -1 WORN
  ECHO PLAYER You fidget and nervously play with the chain around your forehead.
  ECHO OTHERS %n fidgets and nervously plays with the chain around %h forehead.
 ELSE
  ECHO PLAYER You twirl %a about on your index finger.
  ECHO OTHERS %n twirls %a about on %h index finger.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB FLIP -1
 CLEARVERB
 IFITEM -1 WORN
  ECHO PLAYER You flip the catseye set into your ferronniere upside down on your forehead.
  ECHO OTHERS %n flips the catseye set into %h ferronniere upside down on %h forehead.
 ELSE
  ECHO PLAYER You toss %a up into the air and catch it as it comes down.
  ECHO OTHERS %n tosses %a up into the air and catches it as it comes down.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PULL -1
 CLEARVERB
 IFITEM -1 WORN
  ECHO PLAYER You neatly align the jewel on the ferronniere so that it rests perfectly centered upon your brow.
  ECHO OTHERS %n neatly aligns the jewel on %a so that it rests evenly upon %h brow.
 ELSE
  ECHO PLAYER You intertwine the chain of %a around your fingers.
  ECHO OTHERS %n intertwines the delicate chain on %a around %h fingers.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB RUB -1
 CLEARVERB
 IFITEM -1 WORN
  ECHO PLAYER You stroke the catseye set into the ferronniere gently.
  ECHO OTHERS %n strokes the catseye set into %h ferronniere gently.
  PLREVENT 1
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL The eye seems to hum with contained power.
 ELSE
  ECHO PLAYER You polish %a to a high lustre.
  ECHO OTHERS %n carefully polishes %a to a high lustre.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB WEAR -1
 IFITEM -1 WORN
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You fasten %a on your forehead so it is a little more comfortable.
  ECHO OTHERS %n shifts %a on %h forehead so it catches the light dazzlingly.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB CAST -1
 CLEARVERB
 IFVAR SPELLNUM ! 0
  EQUAL SPELLNUM 0
  ECHO PLAYER You gesture at %a.
  ECHO OTHERS %n gestures at %a.
  ECHO ALL The iris within the catseye seems to close.
 ENDIF
ENDIF

INUMBER 771
NAME 899
WEIGHT 1
VOLUME 5
CONTAINER IN
INTERIOR 25
WORN_AROUND
*DESCRIPTION_START
This is a finely made pouch that is clasped at the top with two small
interlocking gold rings. The rings can be aligned so that they will easily
slip through a belt and then securely fastened with a simple twist. The fine
elk leather bunches at the top and smooths out as it reaches to wider base of
the pouch. This is truly a quality item for carrying your wares.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFPREVERB OPEN -1
 CLEARVERB
 IFITEM -1 OPEN
  ECHO PLAYER It's already open.
 ELSE
  ECHO PLAYER You carefully align the two gold rings so that they slip off of your belt easily as %a falls open.
  ECHO OTHERS %n slides two gold rings on %a so that it falls open as it slides off of %h belt.
  OPEN -1
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB CLOSE -1
 CLEARVERB
 IFITEM -1 CLOSED
  ECHO PLAYER It's already closed.
 ELSE
  ECHO PLAYER You close the pouch and lock it shut by slipping the two gold rings through
  ECHO PLAYER the loops.
  ECHO OTHERS %n seals %a shut by slipping the two gold rings through one another.
  CLOSE -1
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB WEAR -1
 IFITEM -1 WORN
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You're already wearing that.
 ELSE
  ECHO PLAYER You slip the two gold rings open as you attach it to your belt.
  ECHO OTHERS %n slips two gold rings on %a open as %s attaches it to %h belt.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
