; Book for Tiewaz
INUMBER 1988
NAME 384
WEIGHT 10
VOLUME 5
INTERIOR 2
OPENABLE
CONTAINER ON
ARTICLE THE
;
IFPREVERB LOOK -1
 IFVAR INTNUM3 = 1
   ECHO PLAYER *** THIS BOOK IS MEANT FOR THE
   ECHO PLAYER     TIEWAZ GUILD AS A ROLE
   ECHO PLAYER     PLAYING DEVICE. DO NOT USE   ***%c
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB OPEN -1
  IFVAR ORG = 27
    IFVAR ITEMBIT1 = 0
      EQUAL ITEMVAL1 1 ;?
      EQUAL ITEMBIT1 1 ;           *** BOOK OPEN ***
      ECHO PLAYER You open %a to the first page.
      ECHO OTHERS %n opens %a and turns to the first page.
      CLEARVERB
    ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER %a is already open.
      CLEARVERB
    ENDIF
  ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER This book was not meant for you.
    ECHO OTHERS %n can't figure out what %a is about.
    CLEARVERB
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB CLOSE -1
  IFVAR ORG = 27
     IFVAR ITEMBIT1 = 1
       EQUAL ITEMBIT1 0 ; book closed
       ECHO PLAYER You close %a.
       ECHO OTHERS %n closes %a.
       CLEARVERB
     ELSE
       ECHO PLAYER %a is already closed.
       CLEARVERB
     ENDIF
  ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER This book was not meant for you.
    ECHO OTHERS %n can't figure out what %a is about.
    CLEARVERB
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB READ -1
   IFVAR ITEMBIT1 = 1
      IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 1
      CLEARVERB
         ECHO OTHERS %n pores over the %a.
         ECHO PLAYER                                                   Page 1%c
         ECHO PLAYER Text copied from a most ancient scroll...%c
         ECHO PLAYER To: Tather Ustos, High Scholar and Archivist, Academy of Knowledge.%c
         ECHO PLAYER        Tather, it is I, Lusier, are you surprised to hear from me after
         ECHO PLAYER so much time. I know many laughed at me when I decided to leave the
         ECHO PLAYER Academies Wall in search of knowledge. But enough!  I can no longer
         ECHO PLAYER contain myself, I am living with a group of Aelfen!  Can you believe it!
         ECHO PLAYER I know you remember me as one who would seldom venture into the rain.
         ECHO PLAYER But I may have changed a bit in the interim. I never would have found
         ECHO PLAYER them, but a young warrior found me. It seems he was on a sort of spirit
         ECHO PLAYER quest, alone, and believed hes duty was to bring me into to the group.
         ECHO PLAYER He would not speak for many leagues. And took me into the Aelfen lands
         ECHO PLAYER which appear to be in a constant state of warfare. We finally reached
         ECHO PLAYER hes group which was strange indeed. It was obvious that this was a sort
         ECHO PLAYER of very elite military unit. But I believe their orders have taken on a
         ECHO PLAYER life of their own. For one thing, it seems they report to no one.
         ECHO PLAYER Thier actions seem to be mainly raids, recons, and strikes against
         ECHO PLAYER specific targets, which they perform where they deem necessary. But
         ECHO PLAYER their actions are thought out and seem very noble. At times though,
         ECHO PLAYER their mystical nature calls out. Tather I tell you the truth, in the
         ECHO PLAYER beginning I thought I may have joined a group of monks!  They have a
         ECHO PLAYER vision/ideal which they call Perth. I do not understand this yet, but
         ECHO PLAYER it involves self-knowledge and acceptance of necessary actions for
         ECHO PLAYER others.
         ECHO PLAYER        But the funniest thing is not them trying to teach me their
         ECHO PLAYER philosophy, it is this; they are trying to teach me their fighting
         ECHO PLAYER style!  Me...Fighting!  It is with normal weapons(though I know not the
         ECHO PLAYER name of them) but has other intricacies. It looks very artful. But for
         ECHO PLAYER now, this is only to tell you I am doing well. I will send a complete
         ECHO PLAYER authropolocical study.
         ECHO PLAYER                                        Yours truly.
         ECHO PLAYER                                          Lusier, Formally of the
         ECHO PLAYER                                            Academy of Knowledge.%c
      ENDIF
      IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 2
      CLEARVERB
         ECHO OTHERS %n pores over the %a.
         ECHO PLAYER                                                   Page 2%c
         ECHO PLAYER Text copied from a wrinkled parchment with dark brown stains...%c
         ECHO PLAYER        I can only take a minute to note this, for night is falling and soon
         ECHO PLAYER serious work begins again. The armys advance has almost been stopped,
         ECHO PLAYER though it still moves with an almost mindless shuffle. The three
         ECHO PLAYER two-man teams had first contact with the army three of four days ago.
         ECHO PLAYER After scouting the group, the teams all had primary and secondary
         ECHO PLAYER targets. The target army proved vulnerable at first and we met with
         ECHO PLAYER early success. We regrouped and repeated our actions many times.
         ECHO PLAYER During the first day and a half we removed most key leaders and all
         ECHO PLAYER mages. But I drift and am turning this into a scouting report. With
         ECHO PLAYER the major brain power af the army removed, it turned into a disorganized
         ECHO PLAYER mass, though still with some force. The time since then has been used
         ECHO PLAYER to remove those who might take command or cause rumors of superstitous
         ECHO PLAYER activities. Though we have been successful, it has cost. Only the
         ECHO PLAYER young initiate Le'Atzu and myself remain. I am steadily bleeding and do
         ECHO PLAYER not expect to reach the dawn. Y'tai Perth. But I wished to leave
         ECHO PLAYER written notice of the young one, Le'Atzu. He is dressed as and easily
         ECHO PLAYER moves amoung the barbarians. But, his endurance and skill are the true
         ECHO PLAYER workings of the art. I can see the light of attainment almost shine
         ECHO PLAYER from him. Though I do not expect either of us to make it out, I commend
         ECHO PLAYER him. He has the potential of greatness.
         ECHO PLAYER     I tire. If the town of outsiders and the valley of Aelfen are to be
         ECHO PLAYER saved, it will be by the grace of this young one.
         ECHO PLAYER                                        Bletit Nee
         ECHO PLAYER                                         Blackshroudsman Y' Perth%c
      ENDIF
      IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 3
       IFVAR RAC = 2
       CLEARVERB
       ECHO OTHERS %n pores over the %a.
         ECHO PLAYER                                                   Page 3%c
         ECHO PLAYER Text copied from a blood tinged parchment...%c
         ECHO PLAYER     My First Student, I have just recieved your note, and I must say it
         ECHO PLAYER greatly troubles me. It is true we have always been an offensive sect,
         ECHO PLAYER and our teachings could be utilized in many different ways. But I do
         ECHO PLAYER not believe the ways you speak are in harmony with our teachings. The
         ECHO PLAYER Perth is but a doorway and Road to a unique view of the world around us.
         ECHO PLAYER I ask of you this, after you present assignment is complete, please
         ECHO PLAYER spend some time in meditation. When you have returned, we will speak.
         ECHO PLAYER                                            Le'Atzu%c
       ELSE
         ECHO PLAYER The text is written in a language foreign to you.
         CLEARVERB
       ENDIF
      ENDIF
      IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 4
       IFVAR RAC = 2
       CLEARVERB
       ECHO OTHERS %n pores over the %a.
         ECHO PLAYER                                                   Page 4%c
         ECHO PLAYER To:   Master Krantioch, Leader of the Moonless rebellion%c
         ECHO PLAYER From: Siltun, Royal Astrologer to King Haussem%c
         ECHO PLAYER     I regret to inform you our agent has failed. He was found dead in an
         ECHO PLAYER ally with his throat cleanly cut. It had the appearance of a simple
         ECHO PLAYER mugging, but this could not be the case. Our assasin had far too much
         ECHO PLAYER skill for this to be true. As this was the third agent to meet such an
         ECHO PLAYER end, I believe we need a new approach. The Kings advisor has long been
         ECHO PLAYER a thorn in our side. Without his advise, the young King could easily be
         ECHO PLAYER manipulated. I believe we need to remove the advisor as well as the
         ECHO PLAYER King, for our revolt to succeed. He is only a meek aelfen scholar,
         ECHO PLAYER perhaps we can get a good price for him in the  market. I have recently
         ECHO PLAYER learned he is friends of a society known as Tiewaz Y' Perth. I believe
         ECHO PLAYER this must be a scholary group of old men who sit around and document
         ECHO PLAYER everything. I only know he recieved a message from them.
         ECHO PLAYER     Anyway, I believe without him, the King could be directed to our
         ECHO PLAYER goals and manipulated. Please send another agent for this and I will
         ECHO PLAYER try to find out who dealt with the other agents. The Kings personal
         ECHO PLAYER guard is still yielding to the blackmail, so I know it is not him nor
         ECHO PLAYER any warrior close.
         ECHO PLAYER                                         Siltun%c
         ECHO PLAYER A note on the bottom written in an old man's handwriting reads:
         ECHO PLAYER Whiteshroudsman Y' Perth,%c
         ECHO PLAYER      One of my scribes recently found this in an old astrology book.
         ECHO PLAYER It reminded me of something that happened in the early days of my reign.
         ECHO PLAYER I though you might find it humorous. Even after all these years, I
         ECHO PLAYER still thank you for my kingdom.    King Haussem.%c
        ELSE
         ECHO PLAYER The text is written in a language foreign to you.
         CLEARVERB
       ENDIF
      ENDIF
  ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER %a is closed.
    CLEARVERB
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB TURN -1
 IFVAR ITEMBIT1 = 1
   IFVAR ORG = 27
     CLEARVERB
     ADD ITEMVAL1 1
     IFVAR ITEMVAL1 > 4
       EQUAL ITEMVAL1 1
       STRCVT 0 ITEMVAL1
       ECHO PLAYER You turn %a to page %0.
       ECHO OTHERS %n turns a page of %a.
       CLEARVERB
     ELSE
       STRCVT 0 ITEMVAL1
       ECHO PLAYER You turn %a to page %0.
       ECHO OTHERS %n turns a page of %a.
       CLEARVERB
     ENDIF
   ELSE
     ECHO PLAYER This book was not meant for you.
     ECHO OTHERS %n can't figure out what %a is about.
     CLEARVERB
   ENDIF
 ELSE
   ECHO PLAYER The book is closed.
   CLEARVERB
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GET -1
 IFVAR INTNUM3 ! 1
  IFVAR ORG ! 27
    ECHO PLAYER %a was not meant for you.
    ECHO OTHERS %n can not figure out what %a is about.
    CLEARVERB
